.\" Manpage for ldms_ls
.\" Contact ovis-help@ca.sandia.gov to correct errors or typos.
.TH man 8 "11 Sep 2014" "1.2" "ldms_ls man page"
.SH NAME
ldms_ls \- Query an ldmsd for metric set values
.SH SYNOPSIS
ldms_ls [OPTION...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
With LDMS (Lightweight Distributed Metric Service), the ldms_ls command is used to query an ldmsd (ldms daemon) for metric set values.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables must be set:
.TP
LD_LIBRARY_PATH
include path to ovis/lib64
.TP
LDMS_XPRT_LIBPATH
path to ovis/lib64/
.TP
LDMSD_PLUGIN_LIBPATH
path to ovis/lib64/
.TP
PATH
include path to ovis/sbin
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h =\flHOST\fR
HOST to query. Default is XXX.
.TP
.BR -x =\flTRANSPORT\fR
TRANSPORT to use for the query. values are sock, rdma, or ugni. Default is sock.
.TP
.BR -p =\flPORT\fR
PORT of the HOST to use for the query. Default is XXX.
.TP
.BR -l 
.br
display long listing. Outputs details of the metric set, including timestamp, metric names, metric types, and values.
.TP
.BR -v
.br
display metadata information
.SH DEFAULTS
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ldms_ls -h vm1 -x sock -p 60000
vm1_1/meminfo
vm1_1/vmstat
.RE
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ldms_ls -h vm1 -x sock-p 60000 -l
vm1_1/meminfo: consistent, last update: Wed Jul 31 21:51:08 2013 [246540us]
U64 33084652         MemTotal
U64 32092964         MemFree
U64 0                Buffers
U64 49244            Cached
U64 0                SwapCached
U64 13536            Active
U64 39844            Inactive
U64 5664             Active(anon)
...
.RE
.PP
.nf
.RS
For a non-existent set:
$ldms_ls -h vm1 -x sock -p 60000 -l vm1_1/foo
ldms_ls: No such file or directory
ldms_ls: lookup failed for set 'vm1_1/foo'
.RE
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
ldmsd(8), ldmsctl(8)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
OVIS Team at Sandia National Laboratories, ABQ NM and Open Grid Computing, Austin TX (ovis-help@sandia.gov)
